{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"18a712bd-a55a-4927-bf57-9290984a9987","content":"The problem is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — a file can only reference modules defined in files listed **above** it. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Domain.fs` is listed second.\n\nFixing by reordering `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01PNUS4HQ3aoVVmpVp6V5m7z","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-dbbb59b9ff1b4047af3a32c7e9e6606a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-dbbb59b9ff1b4047af3a32c7e9e6606a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"fb570318-b213-4a68-8ef6-2ddb21b9d9c8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *above* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but Domain.fs hasn't been compiled yet\n2. Domain.fs\n3. Program.fs\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":365,"requestId":"D818:388A0A:6DD8991:761652E:6A03CBCE"},"id":"1e1da93b-2362-4ccc-92e4-afac83649a9f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:54:45.880Z","parentId":"f0e24d2a-83b7-4cfe-b216-ed716dcb5b84"}
